			      		<p>A 58 year-old man is admitted to the hospital for treatment of acute pulmonary embolism. There are no antecedent risk factors for thrombosis. His coagulation studies at baseline, prior to initiation of anticoagulation, show the following:</p>
			      		<ul>
				      		<li>PT 11 sec (normal 11-15)</li>
